1
00:00:35,041 --> 00:00:37,801
(TICKING)

2
00:00:45,801 --> 00:00:48,521
(TICKING INTENSIFIES)

3
00:00:54,721 --> 00:00:56,761
(SIGHS) Proper.

4
00:00:57,801 --> 00:00:59,401
A-ha!

5
00:00:59,521 --> 00:01:02,161
I said I'd make you
your birthday breakfast.

6
00:01:02,281 --> 00:01:05,161
Yeah, well, I was hungry
and you were dead to the world.

7
00:01:05,281 --> 00:01:06,201
Sorry.

8
00:01:06,321 --> 00:01:08,281
Truckload of presents
should make up for that.

9
00:01:08,401 --> 00:01:09,361
Yeah, about that...

10
00:01:09,481 --> 00:01:11,401
I'm joking!

11
00:01:11,521 --> 00:01:13,441
- No presents. Just a cake.
- Yeah.

12
00:01:14,721 --> 00:01:17,161
- You have got me a cake?
- Yeah, I'm all over the cake.

13
00:01:17,281 --> 00:01:18,521
(LAUGHS)

14
00:01:18,641 --> 00:01:21,281
Mm. Now there's an image!

15
00:01:24,481 --> 00:01:26,161
All right, Monday.

16
00:01:26,281 --> 00:01:28,241
Do your worst.

17
00:01:28,361 --> 00:01:29,561
- Mwah.
- Mwah.

18
00:01:29,681 --> 00:01:31,201
- Have a great day.
- I will.

19
00:01:36,001 --> 00:01:37,241
(DOOR OPENS)

20
00:01:37,361 --> 00:01:38,321
(SIGHS)

21
00:01:38,441 --> 00:01:39,441
(DOOR CLOSES)

22
00:01:45,841 --> 00:01:47,041
(EXHALES)

23
00:01:49,401 --> 00:01:50,801
Whoa! You all right, love?

24
00:01:50,921 --> 00:01:52,721
Hello! Hello!

25
00:01:52,841 --> 00:01:54,201
Hello, pooch.

26
00:01:54,321 --> 00:01:56,161
- Have a leaflet.
- All right. Thanks.

27
00:01:56,281 --> 00:01:57,361
- Morning. Have one of these.
- Thanks.

28
00:01:57,481 --> 00:01:59,721
Hi. You all right?

29
00:01:59,841 --> 00:02:01,081
Morning, Reggie.

30
00:02:04,241 --> 00:02:06,201
(BELL CHIMES)

31
00:02:07,681 --> 00:02:09,601
(EXHALES)

32
00:02:09,721 --> 00:02:12,521
Hello, good morning.
First time in Gloucester?

33
00:02:12,641 --> 00:02:13,761
Try my guided tour.

34
00:02:13,881 --> 00:02:14,961
First time in Gloucester?

35
00:02:15,081 --> 00:02:16,361
Is this your first time
in Gloucester?

36
00:02:16,481 --> 00:02:18,081
Try my guided tour.

37
00:02:18,201 --> 00:02:20,121
This is me. Try my guided tour.

38
00:02:20,241 --> 00:02:23,161
I know all the exciting facts
about Gloucester - yes, I do.

39
00:02:23,281 --> 00:02:24,881
Test me! (LAUGHS)

40
00:02:25,001 --> 00:02:26,681
Go on, then.

41
00:02:26,801 --> 00:02:27,801
Tell me something.

42
00:02:27,921 --> 00:02:28,921
OK.

43
00:02:29,041 --> 00:02:31,601
In 1216, the cathedral hosted

44
00:02:31,721 --> 00:02:33,601
the coronation
of King Henry III,

45
00:02:33,721 --> 00:02:35,841
and he was only nine
at the time! (CHUCKLES)

46
00:02:38,201 --> 00:02:40,201
Th-They filmed Harry Potter
here, too.

47
00:02:40,321 --> 00:02:41,201
Oh!

48
00:02:41,321 --> 00:02:43,441
Yeah, well, plenty more
where that came from.

49
00:02:43,561 --> 00:02:46,401
Tours start at 10.00, 12.00,
and 2.00.

50
00:02:46,521 --> 00:02:47,521
I'll...think about it.

51
00:02:47,641 --> 00:02:49,321
Yeah.

52
00:02:49,441 --> 00:02:51,081
She won't think about it.

53
00:02:51,201 --> 00:02:52,841
No, dear, she won't.

54
00:02:52,961 --> 00:02:54,561
Oh, well. Never mind.

55
00:02:54,681 --> 00:02:56,001
Day's still young.

56
00:03:01,161 --> 00:03:02,481
It's meant to be a heart.

57
00:03:02,601 --> 00:03:04,601
Er... Needs work.

58
00:03:04,721 --> 00:03:07,641
I know. Man spends
his entire life behind a bar -

59
00:03:07,761 --> 00:03:09,801
pivoting to the café trade
ain't easy,

60
00:03:09,921 --> 00:03:11,201
but I try.

61
00:03:12,361 --> 00:03:13,881
For you, I'd try anything.

62
00:03:14,001 --> 00:03:15,961
Allan, we've talked about this.

63
00:03:16,081 --> 00:03:18,961
Oh, I know you're with Lee,
but you deserve better!

64
00:03:19,081 --> 00:03:20,001
Oh.

65
00:03:20,121 --> 00:03:22,081
You know there's
something wrong there.

66
00:03:24,561 --> 00:03:26,761
Is that an actual dossier?

67
00:03:26,881 --> 00:03:29,521
- Yes, on Lee - my Lee dossier.
- Oh, come on!

68
00:03:29,641 --> 00:03:31,241
- He hardly talk to anyone...
- (GASPS)

69
00:03:31,361 --> 00:03:32,921
...cuts his own hair,

70
00:03:33,041 --> 00:03:35,161
gets weird books out
from the library,

71
00:03:35,281 --> 00:03:36,761
claims that his family's
from round here

72
00:03:36,881 --> 00:03:38,241
but I can't find anyone
who knew them.

73
00:03:38,361 --> 00:03:39,761
How can you trust that?

74
00:03:39,881 --> 00:03:41,561
Thank you for
my birthday coffee.

75
00:03:41,681 --> 00:03:43,481
Ruth, I'm telling you,
I hear things.

76
00:03:43,601 --> 00:03:45,721
They don't call me
All Ears Allan for nothin'.

77
00:03:45,841 --> 00:03:49,361
It's not a nickname if you
give it to yourself, is it?

78
00:03:49,481 --> 00:03:51,761
(DOOR BELLS TINKLE)

79
00:04:17,601 --> 00:04:19,321
Ko Fro Lo!

80
00:04:19,441 --> 00:04:22,121
Bo Fro Sho To!

81
00:04:22,241 --> 00:04:24,041
No Bo Ko!

82
00:04:24,161 --> 00:04:25,521
Mo Lo So!

83
00:04:25,641 --> 00:04:27,681
No Kro Do!

84
00:04:48,121 --> 00:04:49,641
She's doing it again.

85
00:04:49,761 --> 00:04:52,241
Spending hours at the controls
looking for something.

86
00:04:52,361 --> 00:04:54,641
Thinks we haven't noticed.

87
00:04:54,761 --> 00:04:56,881
I'll ask her.

88
00:04:57,001 --> 00:04:58,721
Hey, Doc, what are you
looking for?

89
00:05:00,401 --> 00:05:01,561
How long have you been there?

90
00:05:01,681 --> 00:05:02,801
20 minutes.

91
00:05:02,921 --> 00:05:04,401
You haven't.

92
00:05:04,521 --> 00:05:05,401
What you looking for?

93
00:05:05,521 --> 00:05:06,761
Not looking for anything.

94
00:05:06,881 --> 00:05:07,921
Don't lie to us.

95
00:05:13,921 --> 00:05:15,681
The Master.

96
00:05:16,761 --> 00:05:18,081
Why would you do that?

97
00:05:18,201 --> 00:05:19,761
- The Kasaavin took him.
- Yes.

98
00:05:19,881 --> 00:05:21,321
They transported him
to their dimension

99
00:05:21,441 --> 00:05:23,601
and I can't get there
in the TARDIS, but I thought...

100
00:05:23,721 --> 00:05:25,601
...if he escaped,
I could track him.

101
00:05:25,721 --> 00:05:27,401
There's no sign.

102
00:05:27,521 --> 00:05:30,281
I thought he'd be the last
person you'd wanna see.

103
00:05:31,321 --> 00:05:33,321
He left a message for me.

104
00:05:33,441 --> 00:05:34,561
Saying what?

105
00:05:34,681 --> 00:05:36,481
It's personal.

106
00:05:39,361 --> 00:05:40,841
Is that where you go?

107
00:05:42,161 --> 00:05:44,121
When you leave us
to explore and you say

108
00:05:44,241 --> 00:05:45,721
you'll be back in an hour
but you never are?

109
00:05:45,841 --> 00:05:47,281
Are you out looking for him?

110
00:05:48,681 --> 00:05:49,761
Where do you go?

111
00:05:55,721 --> 00:05:56,961
Home.

112
00:06:01,801 --> 00:06:03,641
On my own.

113
00:06:03,761 --> 00:06:05,801
Why? Why not with us?

114
00:06:14,761 --> 00:06:16,801
Cos you ask too many questions.

115
00:06:17,921 --> 00:06:20,681
Maybe because
we're worried about you?

116
00:06:20,801 --> 00:06:22,161
I mean, one minute
you're all smiles,

117
00:06:22,281 --> 00:06:23,801
next minute
your mind's somewhere else.

118
00:06:23,921 --> 00:06:24,841
(ALARM BLARES)

119
00:06:24,961 --> 00:06:27,761
Kro Kro Tro Kro
So Fro So So To!

120
00:06:29,041 --> 00:06:29,961
Kro Kro Tro Kro...

121
00:06:30,081 --> 00:06:31,001
What is that?

122
00:06:31,121 --> 00:06:32,961
A Judoon warning transmission.

123
00:06:33,081 --> 00:06:34,721
The cheek!

124
00:06:34,841 --> 00:06:36,081
Judoon?

125
00:06:36,201 --> 00:06:37,561
Are you just saying that
to shut us up?

126
00:06:37,681 --> 00:06:40,121
Dangerous intergalactic police
for hire.

127
00:06:40,241 --> 00:06:44,241
Notice...of a zonal enforcement
field on Earth -

128
00:06:44,361 --> 00:06:46,441
no-one can get in or out.

129
00:06:46,561 --> 00:06:47,561
What?

130
00:06:47,681 --> 00:06:49,801
They're preparing
to beam down there.

131
00:06:49,921 --> 00:06:52,241
A platoon of Judoon.
Near the moon.

132
00:06:52,361 --> 00:06:55,281
They can't do that. They've got
no jurisdiction there.

133
00:06:55,401 --> 00:06:56,961
Right in the centre
of Gloucester!

134
00:06:57,081 --> 00:06:58,161
I am not having that!

135
00:06:58,281 --> 00:07:00,721
If I can match
the TARDIS's rotation

136
00:07:00,841 --> 00:07:01,761
to the frequency

137
00:07:01,881 --> 00:07:03,721
of the enforcement field's
refresh rate,

138
00:07:03,841 --> 00:07:04,921
I might - just might - be able

139
00:07:05,041 --> 00:07:06,721
to slip us in before
anyone gets killed.

140
00:07:06,841 --> 00:07:08,161
I thought you said
they were the police.

141
00:07:08,281 --> 00:07:10,081
Trigger-happy police.

142
00:07:14,721 --> 00:07:16,601
(ALARM BLARES)

143
00:07:18,921 --> 00:07:20,841
Do Po Lo Sho!

144
00:07:22,281 --> 00:07:25,001
No Dro Fo Ro! Zo!

145
00:07:25,121 --> 00:07:26,241
To Fo Ro!

146
00:07:26,361 --> 00:07:28,001
Dro Ro Fro!

147
00:07:35,681 --> 00:07:37,001
Bo.

148
00:07:38,961 --> 00:07:40,481
Dro!

149
00:07:41,921 --> 00:07:44,281
So 70 Ro!

150
00:07:46,081 --> 00:07:48,721
To Sho Fro!

151
00:07:48,841 --> 00:07:50,881
So Zo To!

152
00:07:53,041 --> 00:07:54,921
No Fo Lo!

153
00:07:55,041 --> 00:07:56,481
(BEEPING)

154
00:07:56,601 --> 00:07:58,441
- (BEEPING)
- No Fo Lo!

155
00:08:00,241 --> 00:08:02,041
No Fo Bo Bo Lo!

156
00:08:02,161 --> 00:08:03,481
Ro!

157
00:08:05,401 --> 00:08:08,441
Bo Ro Kro To Fro Bo!

158
00:08:08,561 --> 00:08:09,841
AN!

159
00:08:09,961 --> 00:08:12,241
- Marcia, don't!
- How dare you!

160
00:08:12,361 --> 00:08:16,281
This is a peaceful, small city.
Who even are you?

161
00:08:18,361 --> 00:08:19,161
Tro Ko Sho.

162
00:08:19,281 --> 00:08:21,081
That took me nine weeks.

163
00:08:22,681 --> 00:08:24,241
RECORDING: That took me
nine weeks.

164
00:08:24,361 --> 00:08:25,881
Language: human.

165
00:08:26,001 --> 00:08:26,921
(BEEPING)

166
00:08:27,041 --> 00:08:28,321
What's this?

167
00:08:28,441 --> 00:08:30,841
Compensation for your weapon.

168
00:08:30,961 --> 00:08:32,641
Answer her question!

169
00:08:32,761 --> 00:08:33,921
Who are you?

170
00:08:35,081 --> 00:08:36,881
We are...

171
00:08:37,001 --> 00:08:38,601
...the Judoon.

172
00:08:40,521 --> 00:08:43,081
Oh...my...God!

173
00:08:43,201 --> 00:08:44,681
You will be catalogued.

174
00:08:44,801 --> 00:08:47,601
I will not! Stay away from me!

175
00:08:47,721 --> 00:08:49,321
- No!
- Marcia!

176
00:08:52,281 --> 00:08:55,681
Enforcement field perimeter
at maximum strength.

177
00:08:55,801 --> 00:08:58,001
You killed her!

178
00:08:59,041 --> 00:09:00,881
Category: human.

179
00:09:01,001 --> 00:09:03,281
- Fugitive match: negative.
- (GROWLS)

180
00:09:04,161 --> 00:09:06,601
- What do you want with us?
- All within the perimeter

181
00:09:06,721 --> 00:09:10,641
must be catalogued.
The fugitive is here.

182
00:09:10,921 --> 00:09:12,961
(DOOR BELLS TINKLE)

183
00:09:14,281 --> 00:09:16,801
Well, look who it isn't...!

184
00:09:16,921 --> 00:09:17,881
I've come to get the cake

185
00:09:18,001 --> 00:09:19,681
that I've ordered
for Ruth's birthday.

186
00:09:19,801 --> 00:09:21,121
Oh, got it right here.

187
00:09:21,241 --> 00:09:22,921
A special birthday message
to her.

188
00:09:27,361 --> 00:09:30,401
What is the matter with you?
Why don't you let it go?

189
00:09:30,521 --> 00:09:31,601
You want to take this outside?

190
00:09:31,721 --> 00:09:32,921
(LAUGHS) Stop asking me that

191
00:09:33,041 --> 00:09:34,841
every time I come in here
for a latte!

192
00:09:34,961 --> 00:09:36,041
(TARDIS THRUMS)

193
00:09:36,161 --> 00:09:37,121
Humans!

194
00:09:37,241 --> 00:09:38,921
- DOCTOR: Through here.
- What are you doing

195
00:09:39,041 --> 00:09:40,161
- in my kitchen?
- Stay inside.

196
00:09:40,281 --> 00:09:42,601
Keep the door closed.
Do not let anyone in,

197
00:09:42,721 --> 00:09:45,401
especially alien police
in helmets and black leather.

198
00:09:46,601 --> 00:09:48,881
The city's under siege.
We're going to sort it.

199
00:09:50,201 --> 00:09:52,441
Oh, yeah, go on,
get out. Coward!

200
00:09:52,561 --> 00:09:54,321
- What is up with him?
- How long you got?

201
00:09:54,441 --> 00:09:55,441
No time at all.

202
00:09:55,561 --> 00:09:56,921
Stay inside. Lock the door.

203
00:09:57,041 --> 00:09:58,241
Come on, gang, no time.

204
00:09:58,361 --> 00:10:01,641
No, no, guys,
look at this little lot.

205
00:10:01,761 --> 00:10:03,841
Lovely! (CHUCKLES)
Look at the state of that!

206
00:10:03,961 --> 00:10:05,721
That's the worst cake
I've ever seen!

207
00:10:08,881 --> 00:10:10,361
Ruth, I've been looking
everywhere for you.

208
00:10:10,481 --> 00:10:12,801
(WHIMPERS) Have you seen?

209
00:10:12,921 --> 00:10:13,681
Yeah.

210
00:10:13,801 --> 00:10:15,001
- They're aliens!
- I know, I know.

211
00:10:15,121 --> 00:10:16,041
Real aliens.

212
00:10:16,161 --> 00:10:17,241
They killed Marcia.

213
00:10:17,361 --> 00:10:18,401
- What?
- Marcia's dead.

214
00:10:18,521 --> 00:10:20,241
We need to get home. Now.

215
00:10:23,561 --> 00:10:24,601
Space rhinos?

216
00:10:25,761 --> 00:10:27,641
I've got no money. I'm sorry,
I'm terrible at this job.

217
00:10:27,761 --> 00:10:30,081
(BEEPING)

218
00:10:30,201 --> 00:10:32,961
Category: human.
Fugitive match: negative.

219
00:10:33,081 --> 00:10:35,361
- Oh, you're after a fugitive?
- (GRUNTS)

220
00:10:35,481 --> 00:10:36,841
I can help. He just left.

221
00:10:36,961 --> 00:10:38,281
On the counter,
there's a dossier.

222
00:10:38,401 --> 00:10:39,841
It's really thorough.

223
00:10:39,961 --> 00:10:41,801
(GRUNTS)

224
00:10:42,801 --> 00:10:45,081
Hey! Watch it, you big...lunk!

225
00:10:48,881 --> 00:10:50,401
Sorry.

226
00:10:50,521 --> 00:10:51,521
Assaulting an officer.

227
00:10:51,641 --> 00:10:53,801
Sentence: execution.

228
00:10:55,121 --> 00:10:56,561
Sentence complete!

229
00:10:58,401 --> 00:10:59,681
OK.

230
00:10:59,801 --> 00:11:02,961
Need to grab some essentials,
a few clothes. We need to go.

231
00:11:03,081 --> 00:11:04,761
What are you talking about?
Go where?

232
00:11:04,881 --> 00:11:06,161
Do you trust me, Ruth?

233
00:11:06,281 --> 00:11:08,281
Sometimes.

234
00:11:09,321 --> 00:11:10,321
You need to just do what I say.

235
00:11:10,441 --> 00:11:12,321
Just get some clothes
and put them in a suitcase.

236
00:11:12,441 --> 00:11:14,721
They can't be after you.
They're aliens.

237
00:11:14,841 --> 00:11:16,521
They've got the heads
of rhinos.

238
00:11:16,641 --> 00:11:18,721
You're from Stroud, Lee.

239
00:11:20,361 --> 00:11:23,041
If there's something
I need to know,

240
00:11:23,161 --> 00:11:25,001
you tell me right now.

241
00:11:29,921 --> 00:11:32,961
There's no time. Come on.

242
00:11:35,161 --> 00:11:37,241
Fugitive house unit located.

243
00:11:37,361 --> 00:11:38,721
Prepare isolator.

244
00:11:38,841 --> 00:11:40,801
I hope you've got
a permit for that.

245
00:11:40,921 --> 00:11:42,801
You're an Imperial Regulator?

246
00:11:42,921 --> 00:11:45,521
Yes. And there's plenty
here to regulate.

247
00:11:45,641 --> 00:11:47,841
For starters, you don't
have jurisdiction here.

248
00:11:47,961 --> 00:11:51,161
So why you're using
a Class Seven Enforcement Field

249
00:11:51,281 --> 00:11:53,161
around this city
bothers me a lot.

250
00:11:53,281 --> 00:11:54,281
More importantly,

251
00:11:54,401 --> 00:11:55,921
this temporal isolator

252
00:11:56,041 --> 00:11:57,761
is an outlawed piece of kit.

253
00:11:57,881 --> 00:12:00,801
Radiation leakage
and civilian casualties.

254
00:12:00,921 --> 00:12:02,281
Designed to freeze time
but causes

255
00:12:02,401 --> 00:12:03,721
horrific collateral damage

256
00:12:03,841 --> 00:12:04,841
to anything and anyone

257
00:12:04,961 --> 00:12:06,441
that gets in its path.
Horrible thing.

258
00:12:06,561 --> 00:12:08,001
Hey, you're not using
that thing here, pal,

259
00:12:08,121 --> 00:12:10,921
so consider your rhino backside
imperially regulated.

260
00:12:11,041 --> 00:12:12,401
(SNARLS)

261
00:12:12,521 --> 00:12:13,841
It sounded tougher in me head.

262
00:12:13,961 --> 00:12:17,641
Fugitive is highly dangerous.
Precautions must be taken.

263
00:12:17,761 --> 00:12:21,681
Not that weapon, not here.
Humans will die, and you,

264
00:12:21,801 --> 00:12:23,761
Captain, will have racked up
enough violations

265
00:12:23,881 --> 00:12:26,041
to ensure that your troop
never get hired again.

266
00:12:26,161 --> 00:12:27,041
(GROWLS)

267
00:12:27,161 --> 00:12:30,601
Look at you and your platoon
of Judoon near the...

268
00:12:31,961 --> 00:12:32,881
...that lagoon.

269
00:12:33,001 --> 00:12:34,041
More of a canal.

270
00:12:34,161 --> 00:12:35,801
- RYAN: Yeah.
- Where's your pride?

271
00:12:35,921 --> 00:12:37,281
(GROWLS)

272
00:12:37,401 --> 00:12:39,201
Where's your respect
for the rules?

273
00:12:39,321 --> 00:12:40,961
I'm very disappointed in you.

274
00:12:41,081 --> 00:12:42,401
(GRUNTS)

275
00:12:42,521 --> 00:12:44,121
So, we will take over from
here.

276
00:12:44,241 --> 00:12:45,401
Negative!

277
00:12:45,521 --> 00:12:48,081
Mission must be fulfilled
by the contracted troop.

278
00:12:48,201 --> 00:12:51,361
Judoon Engagement Article 163B!

279
00:12:51,481 --> 00:12:53,761
That article...is overridden

280
00:12:53,881 --> 00:12:55,281
by local Earth law...

281
00:12:55,401 --> 00:12:56,321
-12...

282
00:12:56,441 --> 00:12:57,841
(GRUNTS)

283
00:12:57,961 --> 00:13:00,681
...which clearly states
that any potential arrestee

284
00:13:00,801 --> 00:13:03,161
is entitled to arbitration
with a third party.

285
00:13:03,281 --> 00:13:04,721
Isn't that correct,

286
00:13:04,841 --> 00:13:06,521
Liaison Officer Khan?

287
00:13:06,641 --> 00:13:08,881
Absolutely correct. 100%.

288
00:13:09,001 --> 00:13:11,041
Rule 127 Massive.

289
00:13:11,161 --> 00:13:12,881
Imperial regulation.

290
00:13:13,001 --> 00:13:16,361
So you will give us the time
to go in there and arbitrate.

291
00:13:16,481 --> 00:13:18,401
That weapon will not
need to be used.

292
00:13:18,521 --> 00:13:20,081
- Clear?
- (GRUNTS)

293
00:13:20,201 --> 00:13:23,641
Come on! We can sort this,
woman to woman.

294
00:13:25,161 --> 00:13:26,321
Give me ten Earth minutes

295
00:13:26,441 --> 00:13:27,881
and we can have this
resolved for you.

296
00:13:29,481 --> 00:13:30,401
Five minutes.

297
00:13:30,521 --> 00:13:31,561
- Nine.
- Four!

298
00:13:31,681 --> 00:13:33,361
Er, fine. I'll take five.

299
00:13:33,481 --> 00:13:35,161
I hate it when they do that.

300
00:13:35,281 --> 00:13:37,561
We'd best take the lift.
Hang on, where's Graham?

301
00:13:37,681 --> 00:13:39,241
- I don't know.
- Have you lost him?

302
00:13:39,361 --> 00:13:40,361
He's not my responsibility.

303
00:13:40,481 --> 00:13:42,801
He's always a few steps behind.
I've stopped checking.

304
00:13:42,921 --> 00:13:43,961
Four minutes thirty.

305
00:13:44,081 --> 00:13:46,441
We haven't started yet!
Come on.

306
00:13:48,561 --> 00:13:51,281
(GROANS)

307
00:14:02,121 --> 00:14:03,321
(AMERICAN ACCENT) Don't move.

308
00:14:03,441 --> 00:14:05,801
Seriously, not a muscle.

309
00:14:05,921 --> 00:14:07,641
Working on
the movement sensors.

310
00:14:07,761 --> 00:14:10,561
If you even flinch,
it'll set off the laser spikes.

311
00:14:10,681 --> 00:14:13,321
Trust me, they get everywhere.

312
00:14:13,441 --> 00:14:16,241
By the way, lookin' good.

313
00:14:16,361 --> 00:14:18,841
Who is this? What's going on?

314
00:14:18,961 --> 00:14:20,641
Where am I? And where are you?

315
00:14:21,921 --> 00:14:23,721
Neutralised.

316
00:14:23,841 --> 00:14:25,681
Comin' to join you.

317
00:14:25,801 --> 00:14:27,921
You can get excited now.

318
00:14:28,041 --> 00:14:31,161
Ha! You missed me, right?

319
00:14:32,321 --> 00:14:33,681
Ha-ha!

320
00:14:39,641 --> 00:14:41,041
Have we met?

321
00:14:42,081 --> 00:14:44,361
Still cheeky.
Regeneration can't change that.

322
00:14:44,481 --> 00:14:45,721
Gotta say, loving the grey

323
00:14:45,841 --> 00:14:47,041
at the temple.

324
00:14:47,161 --> 00:14:49,721
Kinda distinguished,
yet still sexy.

325
00:14:50,441 --> 00:14:52,321
- Oh, come here!
- Whoa!

326
00:14:55,041 --> 00:14:57,241
How you been, Doctor?

327
00:14:57,361 --> 00:14:58,521
Ah.

328
00:14:59,801 --> 00:15:03,561
Pay attention, cos every word
I'm about to say is true.

329
00:15:03,681 --> 00:15:05,841
There's a nasty bunch
of alien police outside.

330
00:15:05,961 --> 00:15:08,881
They're pointing a highly
dangerous cannon at this flat,

331
00:15:09,001 --> 00:15:11,761
and they'll fire it
in about, er, four minutes.

332
00:15:11,881 --> 00:15:14,161
I might be able to stop them,
but I need to understand

333
00:15:14,281 --> 00:15:17,041
exactly why they're here, so
you need to let us in, quick.

334
00:15:20,001 --> 00:15:21,481
Right, tell us everything.

335
00:15:21,601 --> 00:15:23,281
Who are you? We need to leave!

336
00:15:23,401 --> 00:15:25,241
Right into the arms of
intergalactic mercenaries

337
00:15:25,361 --> 00:15:28,521
who seem to think you are
a fugitive from justice.

338
00:15:28,641 --> 00:15:30,321
- They've got it wrong.
- Sure about that?

339
00:15:30,441 --> 00:15:31,881
Yeah! It's mistaken identity.

340
00:15:32,001 --> 00:15:34,321
He works at Bathrooms4U,
for God's sake!

341
00:15:34,441 --> 00:15:36,921
You'd better be telling
the truth, both of you,

342
00:15:37,041 --> 00:15:38,801
otherwise the Judoon
will have you

343
00:15:38,921 --> 00:15:41,601
for harbouring the fugitive,
and their justice is brutal.

344
00:15:41,721 --> 00:15:43,561
I'm not harbouring anyone!

345
00:15:43,681 --> 00:15:46,081
If you're both so innocent,
why are your bags packed?

346
00:15:46,201 --> 00:15:47,721
Yeah, like you're about to
go on the run.

347
00:15:47,841 --> 00:15:49,841
Khan and Sinclair
with the key questions.

348
00:15:49,961 --> 00:15:51,201
Not that you'll get very far,

349
00:15:51,321 --> 00:15:53,641
given the enforcement perimeter
they've just knocked up.

350
00:15:53,761 --> 00:15:54,961
Come on, quick with the truth!

351
00:15:55,081 --> 00:15:57,241
We've got about three minutes,
probably less.

352
00:15:57,361 --> 00:15:58,921
What are you hiding?

353
00:15:59,041 --> 00:16:00,161
Check the flat,

354
00:16:00,281 --> 00:16:01,281
see what's here.

355
00:16:01,401 --> 00:16:02,921
If it isn't these two, it could
be something inside here.

356
00:16:03,041 --> 00:16:04,081
You're not
going through my flat!

357
00:16:04,201 --> 00:16:05,041
Yes, they are.

358
00:16:05,161 --> 00:16:06,481
Have you seen
those things outside?

359
00:16:06,601 --> 00:16:07,881
Yeah, and I've seen
what they do,

360
00:16:08,001 --> 00:16:09,201
and that's why we're running.

361
00:16:09,321 --> 00:16:10,321
- (SONIC WHIRS)
- What are you doing?

362
00:16:10,441 --> 00:16:13,161
- What is that?!
- A device that tells me...

363
00:16:16,201 --> 00:16:19,081
...you're both
completely human.

364
00:16:20,241 --> 00:16:21,801
Please,

365
00:16:21,921 --> 00:16:24,921
I'm trying to save a lot of
lives here, including yours.

366
00:16:25,041 --> 00:16:27,601
If you have any idea why
the Judoon are pursuing you,

367
00:16:27,721 --> 00:16:29,601
you have to tell me right now.

368
00:16:34,801 --> 00:16:37,281
What the...?
What's happening out there?

369
00:16:37,401 --> 00:16:39,001
I guess they want
their ship back.

370
00:16:39,121 --> 00:16:40,241
What, this ain't your ship?

371
00:16:40,361 --> 00:16:41,601
You think I'd choose this look?

372
00:16:41,721 --> 00:16:43,401
Doesn't even have a bar!

373
00:16:44,921 --> 00:16:46,161
A little evasive action.

374
00:16:46,281 --> 00:16:49,921
Hoping these shields
are as good as they say.

375
00:16:50,041 --> 00:16:51,801
A few battles
going on around us...

376
00:16:52,801 --> 00:16:56,361
You're not just kidding me?
You're really not the Doctor?

377
00:16:56,481 --> 00:16:59,241
Oh, no, no. My name's Graham.
I just travel with the Doc.

378
00:16:59,361 --> 00:17:02,681
Ha! Which is why the scoop
read the wrong signal!

379
00:17:02,801 --> 00:17:04,441
Ho-ho, using the old
Quanticum Scoop

380
00:17:04,561 --> 00:17:07,041
I got from a fourple
on Ibiza 13... Whoo!

381
00:17:07,161 --> 00:17:09,161
That was a night!

382
00:17:09,281 --> 00:17:11,401
Actually, that was a month.

383
00:17:11,521 --> 00:17:13,921
Well, look, now you know
who I am, tell me who you are,

384
00:17:14,041 --> 00:17:16,001
why you've kidnapped me
and why you're after the Doc.

385
00:17:16,121 --> 00:17:18,001
I mean, we're in the middle
of something right now.

386
00:17:18,121 --> 00:17:20,361
Captain Jack Harkness
at your service.

387
00:17:20,481 --> 00:17:22,721
Me and the Doc, we go way back.

388
00:17:22,841 --> 00:17:23,801
This is important.

389
00:17:23,921 --> 00:17:27,081
He needs to know the future
of the universe is at stake.

390
00:17:27,201 --> 00:17:28,441
Not he, she.

391
00:17:28,561 --> 00:17:30,721
(LAUGHS)

392
00:17:30,841 --> 00:17:31,921
Oh!

393
00:17:33,161 --> 00:17:34,201
This I gotta see.

394
00:17:35,401 --> 00:17:37,961
Temporal isolator primed,
Captain.

395
00:17:38,081 --> 00:17:40,721
Prepare Final Warning Missile.

396
00:17:42,281 --> 00:17:43,321
Find anything?

397
00:17:43,441 --> 00:17:44,641
A few cash-flow problems,

398
00:17:44,761 --> 00:17:46,721
a collection of old phones
and keys.

399
00:17:46,841 --> 00:17:48,361
I found this in the bedroom.

400
00:17:48,481 --> 00:17:50,561
Hollow compartment
at the back of the wardrobe.

401
00:17:50,681 --> 00:17:51,801
(SONIC WHIRS)

402
00:17:51,921 --> 00:17:53,201
And that...

403
00:17:53,321 --> 00:17:54,601
...is not from Earth.

404
00:17:54,721 --> 00:17:56,121
So where's it from?

405
00:17:56,241 --> 00:17:58,281
- (WHOOSHING)
- (GLASS SHATTERS)

406
00:17:58,401 --> 00:18:00,241
- Oh, my God!
- What was that?!

407
00:18:00,361 --> 00:18:02,201
This came flying
through the window.

408
00:18:02,321 --> 00:18:04,721
Isolation of fugitive
housing unit

409
00:18:04,841 --> 00:18:06,841
in 108 seconds.

410
00:18:06,961 --> 00:18:08,681
Doesn't time fly when you don't
have all the answers?

411
00:18:08,801 --> 00:18:10,881
So, anyone know what this is?

412
00:18:11,001 --> 00:18:12,241
No, I've never seen it before.

413
00:18:12,361 --> 00:18:14,001
Me neither.

414
00:18:15,401 --> 00:18:16,761
We found it hidden
in your bedroom.

415
00:18:17,641 --> 00:18:18,961
You'd better be
telling the truth,

416
00:18:19,081 --> 00:18:20,441
cos there's a lot of
innocent people

417
00:18:20,561 --> 00:18:22,361
that could die if we don't
sort this out quick.

418
00:18:22,481 --> 00:18:23,521
92 seconds.

419
00:18:29,121 --> 00:18:30,641
Give me the box.

420
00:18:32,561 --> 00:18:33,561
82 seconds.

421
00:18:33,681 --> 00:18:35,881
Give me the box.

422
00:18:36,001 --> 00:18:38,601
- Lee? What is that?
- It's nothing.

423
00:18:38,721 --> 00:18:40,441
No, it clearly is something,

424
00:18:40,561 --> 00:18:42,841
cos suddenly you're
all bothered about it,

425
00:18:42,961 --> 00:18:44,601
and I've never seen it
before in my life.

426
00:18:46,681 --> 00:18:47,761
You're in charge, right?

427
00:18:47,881 --> 00:18:49,441
It's a very flat
team structure.

428
00:18:49,561 --> 00:18:52,041
You're the smartest.
I can see it in your eyes.

429
00:18:52,161 --> 00:18:55,201
Use the fire exit out the back.
Take Ruth.

430
00:18:55,321 --> 00:18:57,281
Get her out
and make sure she's OK.

431
00:18:57,401 --> 00:18:58,521
I can take care of this.

432
00:18:58,641 --> 00:19:00,001
What? No, you can't!

433
00:19:00,121 --> 00:19:02,161
What's in the box, Lee?
Who are you really?

434
00:19:02,281 --> 00:19:03,481
It's none of your business.

435
00:19:06,561 --> 00:19:08,641
You've got half of Gloucester
under Judoon lockdown.

436
00:19:08,761 --> 00:19:10,001
I'm making it my business.

437
00:19:10,121 --> 00:19:11,361
45 seconds.

438
00:19:11,481 --> 00:19:13,761
I can deal with this.

439
00:19:13,881 --> 00:19:16,081
Just take Ruth.

440
00:19:16,201 --> 00:19:17,481
40 seconds.

441
00:19:17,601 --> 00:19:19,601
Look, I've...
I've made a mistake.

442
00:19:21,081 --> 00:19:23,161
You're the most important thing
in my life.

443
00:19:24,161 --> 00:19:25,641
I can't let others
lose their lives.

444
00:19:25,761 --> 00:19:27,441
I need to make sure
you're safe.

445
00:19:27,561 --> 00:19:28,361
What do you mean, "a mistake"?

446
00:19:28,481 --> 00:19:30,721
I just need
to talk to them, OK?

447
00:19:30,841 --> 00:19:32,361
But they're space rhinos, Lee.

448
00:19:32,481 --> 00:19:33,521
What are you going to
chat to them about?

449
00:19:33,641 --> 00:19:35,401
- 23 seconds.
- They'll see us

450
00:19:35,521 --> 00:19:36,761
getting out of the fire escape.

451
00:19:36,881 --> 00:19:38,481
- Unless...
- (TOGETHER) Diversion!

452
00:19:38,601 --> 00:19:39,721
Look, you take Ruth.
We'll go out the front

453
00:19:39,841 --> 00:19:40,921
and distract the space feds.

454
00:19:41,041 --> 00:19:42,081
- You think that'll work?
- Come on!

455
00:19:42,201 --> 00:19:43,721
No, cos I'm not going anywhere
without Lee.

456
00:19:43,841 --> 00:19:45,801
I'm a police officer.
I speak their language.

457
00:19:45,921 --> 00:19:47,761
A bit of stalling,
buy time to get them away.

458
00:19:47,881 --> 00:19:50,041
Then we can come inside
with them and be by your side.

459
00:19:50,161 --> 00:19:51,441
I don't need you to be here.

460
00:19:51,561 --> 00:19:52,521
You obviously do,

461
00:19:52,641 --> 00:19:54,361
because there's a cannon
about to fire at your flat.

462
00:19:54,481 --> 00:19:57,721
Time limit exceeded.
Initiating temporal isolation.

463
00:19:57,841 --> 00:19:58,881
We're out of time.

464
00:19:59,001 --> 00:20:00,561
It's the best plan we've got
for keeping this block safe.

465
00:20:00,681 --> 00:20:02,081
Right, be careful.

466
00:20:02,201 --> 00:20:04,481
The Judoon might look dumb,
but they're deadly.

467
00:20:04,601 --> 00:20:06,201
Go to the cathedral.
I'll meet you there.

468
00:20:06,321 --> 00:20:07,481
- OK?
- You better.

469
00:20:07,601 --> 00:20:09,681
Not going to miss
your birthday, am I?

470
00:20:09,801 --> 00:20:11,001
Go, go, go,

471
00:20:11,121 --> 00:20:12,641
before they launch that thing.

472
00:20:12,761 --> 00:20:13,961
...Full documentation
available on request.

473
00:20:14,081 --> 00:20:15,081
See you at the cathedral.

474
00:20:15,201 --> 00:20:17,161
Activate Temporal Blast.

475
00:20:17,281 --> 00:20:19,161
(WHIRRING)

476
00:20:19,281 --> 00:20:20,881
Stop!

477
00:20:21,001 --> 00:20:22,321
Arbitration complete.

478
00:20:22,441 --> 00:20:23,801
Arbitration result?

479
00:20:23,921 --> 00:20:25,401
You can come in now.

480
00:20:25,521 --> 00:20:27,201
So long as you turn that off.

481
00:20:27,321 --> 00:20:30,161
Pause isolation. Remain here.

482
00:20:30,281 --> 00:20:32,521
No fugitives in there,
by the way.

483
00:20:32,641 --> 00:20:34,121
(GROWLS)

484
00:20:34,241 --> 00:20:35,881
And as for you lot,

485
00:20:36,001 --> 00:20:37,641
I don't want you using that.

486
00:20:47,641 --> 00:20:49,561
Keeping my promise.

487
00:20:51,081 --> 00:20:52,441
(PHONE BEEPS)

488
00:20:53,441 --> 00:20:55,201
- (CRASHING)
- JUDOON: Surrender!

489
00:20:55,321 --> 00:20:58,001
This property now
under Judoon jurisdiction.

490
00:21:01,041 --> 00:21:03,761
I surrender. OK?

491
00:21:03,881 --> 00:21:06,841
You can tell your boss.
You-You got me.

492
00:21:10,361 --> 00:21:12,481
- YAZ: Graham!
- RYAN: What just happened?

493
00:21:12,601 --> 00:21:13,881
What are we doing here?

494
00:21:14,001 --> 00:21:18,241
Short answers - this guy,
stolen ship, being fired at.

495
00:21:18,361 --> 00:21:20,481
We need to get back.
And who are you?

496
00:21:20,601 --> 00:21:22,801
Young. I like you young.

497
00:21:22,921 --> 00:21:25,841
But silver fox said,
"She, not he."

498
00:21:25,961 --> 00:21:29,201
So you, not you, right?

499
00:21:29,321 --> 00:21:30,521
I hope you kept

500
00:21:30,641 --> 00:21:31,761
the receipt for the scoop.

501
00:21:31,881 --> 00:21:33,841
Seriously? Three of you?

502
00:21:33,961 --> 00:21:35,601
I had a dream about this once.

503
00:21:35,721 --> 00:21:37,001
- (SUDDEN CRASH)
- Whoa!

504
00:21:37,121 --> 00:21:39,001
- Hold on to something.
- (ALARM BLARES)

505
00:21:39,121 --> 00:21:41,961
JUDOON: Incoming matter
transmission.

506
00:21:43,401 --> 00:21:46,481
Commander Gat,
your presence is not required.

507
00:21:46,601 --> 00:21:48,841
Could've fooled me.
I've been watching it all.

508
00:21:48,961 --> 00:21:50,041
You're so noisy.

509
00:21:50,161 --> 00:21:52,041
Talk about sledgehammers
to crack a nut.

510
00:21:55,921 --> 00:21:59,401
Presenting occupant
of housing unit.

511
00:21:59,521 --> 00:22:01,641
Hello, old friend.

512
00:22:01,761 --> 00:22:03,201
I see you're back
from the dead.

513
00:22:04,561 --> 00:22:06,681
We had such a moving funeral
for you.

514
00:22:07,681 --> 00:22:09,841
But I suppose
that was your intention.

515
00:22:10,761 --> 00:22:13,241
Did you really think
that we wouldn't find you?

516
00:22:14,241 --> 00:22:16,241
Did you think that I'd ever
stop looking?

517
00:22:17,361 --> 00:22:22,041
Good place to hide, mind, the
far backside of a tiny galaxy.

518
00:22:22,161 --> 00:22:24,481
How did you find me?

519
00:22:28,161 --> 00:22:30,481
Sentiment was always
going to be your downfall.

520
00:22:30,601 --> 00:22:32,041
You kept it.

521
00:22:32,161 --> 00:22:33,081
Silly.

522
00:22:33,201 --> 00:22:35,081
Chronotelluric alloy,
strong entanglement.

523
00:22:35,201 --> 00:22:38,201
Very trackable.
It just takes a while.

524
00:22:42,961 --> 00:22:44,161
Yeah, well...

525
00:22:45,201 --> 00:22:46,441
...] wanted to repair it...

526
00:22:47,721 --> 00:22:48,721
...polish it.

527
00:22:48,841 --> 00:22:50,961
My service medal.

528
00:22:51,081 --> 00:22:53,521
Honour and courage
still mean something.

529
00:22:53,641 --> 00:22:54,721
I agree.

530
00:22:56,161 --> 00:22:58,801
See, this is the problem
with our identical training.

531
00:23:00,721 --> 00:23:02,481
We share all the same tricks.

532
00:23:04,041 --> 00:23:05,041
Kill him.

533
00:23:06,281 --> 00:23:09,081
Detained fugitive must be
transferred to contracted...

534
00:23:09,201 --> 00:23:11,481
No, idiot.
You didn't scan him yet,

535
00:23:11,601 --> 00:23:12,681
- did you?
- Uh-uh.

536
00:23:14,241 --> 00:23:16,401
Bless.

537
00:23:16,521 --> 00:23:17,521
(BEEPING)

538
00:23:19,681 --> 00:23:21,721
Fugitive: negative.

539
00:23:21,841 --> 00:23:23,161
Explain.

540
00:23:23,281 --> 00:23:25,161
I'm sorry it has to
end this way.

541
00:23:25,281 --> 00:23:27,201
You got so close to escaping.

542
00:23:28,441 --> 00:23:30,041
Faithful companion.

543
00:23:32,081 --> 00:23:34,561
(GROWLS)

544
00:23:34,681 --> 00:23:36,641
Do I have to spell it out
for you?

545
00:23:39,001 --> 00:23:42,441
(BELLS PEAL)

546
00:23:47,601 --> 00:23:48,681
All clear.

547
00:23:50,881 --> 00:23:53,081
Now, you need to tell me
everything you know about Lee -

548
00:23:53,201 --> 00:23:56,161
how long you've been together,
and what was that metallic box?

549
00:23:56,281 --> 00:23:57,561
- Er...
- (PHONE CHIMES)

550
00:23:57,681 --> 00:23:59,081
(UNZIPS POCKET)

551
00:24:05,121 --> 00:24:06,681
(ECHOING WHISPERS)

552
00:24:07,721 --> 00:24:09,961
- Is that from Lee?
- No.

553
00:24:10,081 --> 00:24:11,481
It's...nothing.

554
00:24:16,841 --> 00:24:18,881
JUDOON: This cathedral
is under Judoon control.

555
00:24:19,001 --> 00:24:21,921
All occupants must
surrender immediately.

556
00:24:22,041 --> 00:24:25,081
There will be no escape
this time.

557
00:24:25,201 --> 00:24:27,241
We have you surrounded.

558
00:24:30,001 --> 00:24:31,241
How can I help?

559
00:24:31,361 --> 00:24:32,961
You interfered, Regulator.

560
00:24:33,081 --> 00:24:34,401
You know what they say,

561
00:24:34,521 --> 00:24:37,161
one person's arbitration is
another person's interference.

562
00:24:37,281 --> 00:24:38,641
Very blurry line.

563
00:24:39,801 --> 00:24:41,561
This is a place of worship.

564
00:24:41,681 --> 00:24:43,801
Show some respect,
or I'll overload

565
00:24:43,921 --> 00:24:45,921
those guns and make it
a bad day for everyone.

566
00:24:46,041 --> 00:24:49,641
Now, let's go,
and nobody needs to get hurt.

567
00:24:49,761 --> 00:24:51,201
What have you done with Lee?

568
00:24:51,321 --> 00:24:53,201
Information request granted.

569
00:24:54,801 --> 00:24:56,241
(BEEPING)

570
00:24:56,361 --> 00:24:58,281
Sentence: execution.

571
00:24:58,401 --> 00:24:59,961
You murdered him.

572
00:25:02,521 --> 00:25:05,121
That is a violation
of your contract!

573
00:25:05,241 --> 00:25:06,561
Incorrect.

574
00:25:06,681 --> 00:25:09,321
Contract stated
retrieval of fugitive.

575
00:25:09,441 --> 00:25:11,801
Fugitive identified.

576
00:25:14,361 --> 00:25:16,441
- What?
- Biological shielding

577
00:25:16,561 --> 00:25:17,761
decrypted.

578
00:25:17,881 --> 00:25:19,521
Fugitive: positive.

579
00:25:27,241 --> 00:25:30,761
That's it. Back up
or Daddy Rhinoform gets it.

580
00:25:32,321 --> 00:25:33,721
What are you doing?!

581
00:25:33,841 --> 00:25:36,361
It feels like...instinct

582
00:25:36,481 --> 00:25:38,641
against the bullies.

583
00:25:38,761 --> 00:25:40,561
Cos you know
the thing about bullies?

584
00:25:40,681 --> 00:25:42,361
There's always a weak spot.

585
00:25:43,481 --> 00:25:46,121
(ROARS)

586
00:25:46,241 --> 00:25:48,361
Bo! Ko! Fo! Jo! To!

587
00:25:54,961 --> 00:25:56,441
Do you know
what you've just done?

588
00:25:57,681 --> 00:25:58,681
Who agre you?!

589
00:26:06,201 --> 00:26:09,561
You have to get us back there.
The Doctor needs us.

590
00:26:09,681 --> 00:26:12,281
Listen, kid, working with
some low-rent equipment here.

591
00:26:12,401 --> 00:26:13,921
Why doesn't that surprise me?

592
00:26:14,041 --> 00:26:16,161
Oh, she likes them mouthy,
then, huh?

593
00:26:16,281 --> 00:26:18,041
Yeah, one up from cheesy.

594
00:26:18,161 --> 00:26:20,801
OK, he's my favourite. (LAUGHS)

595
00:26:20,921 --> 00:26:22,201
(SUDDEN CRASH)

596
00:26:22,321 --> 00:26:23,881
Whoo!

597
00:26:24,001 --> 00:26:26,201
Why didn't it scoop her?
Why can't I get her here?

598
00:26:26,321 --> 00:26:28,281
(SHOUTS IN FRUSTRATION)

599
00:26:28,401 --> 00:26:31,241
Are there Judoon anywhere near
where I scooped you?

600
00:26:31,361 --> 00:26:32,841
Yeah! A lot.

601
00:26:32,961 --> 00:26:34,721
Oh, I knew it!

602
00:26:34,841 --> 00:26:36,121
Level Seven Enforcement Field.

603
00:26:36,241 --> 00:26:38,281
That's why I can't get
accurate traces on her.

604
00:26:38,401 --> 00:26:40,201
Interfering with everything.

605
00:26:41,801 --> 00:26:43,081
Is she safe?

606
00:26:43,201 --> 00:26:45,321
(BELLS CHIME)

607
00:26:53,001 --> 00:26:55,841
(SONIC WHIRS)

608
00:26:57,361 --> 00:27:00,001
Total Judoon evacuation.

609
00:27:01,721 --> 00:27:04,041
They've even removed
the enforcement perimeter.

610
00:27:04,161 --> 00:27:05,961
That's got to be good?

611
00:27:06,081 --> 00:27:08,281
No! Judoon switching strategy

612
00:27:08,401 --> 00:27:11,041
means things have got very bad
and very personal now.

613
00:27:11,161 --> 00:27:12,601
Ruth...

614
00:27:12,721 --> 00:27:14,801
...you just dishonoured
a Judoon captain,

615
00:27:14,921 --> 00:27:17,801
and removing their horn
is the worst insult.

616
00:27:19,321 --> 00:27:21,281
I think you know far more
than you're telling me

617
00:27:21,401 --> 00:27:24,441
about Lee and about
why the Judoon are here.

618
00:27:24,561 --> 00:27:26,041
It's time to share.

619
00:27:26,161 --> 00:27:27,761
I don't know anything.

620
00:27:28,761 --> 00:27:31,841
I don't even know how I did
what I just did to them.

621
00:27:31,961 --> 00:27:34,201
(SONIC WHIRS)

622
00:27:34,321 --> 00:27:36,721
I don't have the decryption
for your bio-shield.

623
00:27:38,041 --> 00:27:40,041
You and Lee
must have both had them.

624
00:27:40,161 --> 00:27:43,921
Very sophisticated,
like biological cloaking.

625
00:27:45,281 --> 00:27:46,401
Look at me.

626
00:27:46,521 --> 00:27:48,081
I know my own life.

627
00:27:49,521 --> 00:27:51,281
I'm Ruth Clayton.

628
00:27:51,401 --> 00:27:52,801
I am 44.

629
00:27:52,921 --> 00:27:54,361
I'm married.

630
00:27:54,481 --> 00:27:55,881
I'm a tour guide.

631
00:27:56,001 --> 00:27:57,641
And I am scared!

632
00:27:58,761 --> 00:28:00,321
Back then...

633
00:28:00,441 --> 00:28:01,641
...that was not me.

634
00:28:01,761 --> 00:28:04,041
My hands, they just moved.
They...

635
00:28:04,161 --> 00:28:06,041
Well, if it wasn't you,
who was it?

636
00:28:06,161 --> 00:28:07,321
I don't know.

637
00:28:07,441 --> 00:28:09,401
I don't understand any of this.
None of this is me.

638
00:28:09,521 --> 00:28:10,921
It can't be.

639
00:28:11,921 --> 00:28:12,921
Help me.

640
00:28:15,081 --> 00:28:16,401
Show me your phone.

641
00:28:16,521 --> 00:28:17,441
You received a message

642
00:28:17,561 --> 00:28:19,361
just before you turned into
Jackie Chan.

643
00:28:19,481 --> 00:28:22,321
"Follow the light.
Break the glass.”

644
00:28:22,441 --> 00:28:23,361
Ruth...

645
00:28:23,481 --> 00:28:24,961
...I don't think you are

646
00:28:25,081 --> 00:28:27,641
who you say you are
or who you think you are.

647
00:28:27,761 --> 00:28:30,761
I think there's another
identity hidden within you.

648
00:28:32,321 --> 00:28:35,721
Maybe this text is
an activation message...

649
00:28:35,841 --> 00:28:38,041
...words to trigger
the real you,

650
00:28:38,161 --> 00:28:40,681
the instincts that enabled you
to attack the Judoon.

651
00:28:40,801 --> 00:28:43,121
No. I'm not that person.

652
00:28:43,241 --> 00:28:44,761
I don't want to be that person.

653
00:28:44,881 --> 00:28:47,441
I'm afraid you don't have
a choice!

654
00:28:47,561 --> 00:28:50,321
Do you have any idea
what this means?

655
00:28:50,441 --> 00:28:52,561
The light. The glass.

656
00:28:52,681 --> 00:28:54,801
(BELL CHIMES)

657
00:28:57,121 --> 00:28:59,241
(ECHOING WHISPERS)

658
00:29:00,441 --> 00:29:02,481
Yeah, I do.

659
00:29:02,601 --> 00:29:03,761
I just saw it.

660
00:29:05,121 --> 00:29:06,361
But it's just a memory.

661
00:29:06,481 --> 00:29:07,481
A memory of what?

662
00:29:07,601 --> 00:29:10,761
The lighthouse where I grew up,

663
00:29:10,881 --> 00:29:12,361
my family home.

664
00:29:14,201 --> 00:29:16,721
Why am I seeing that now?

665
00:29:16,841 --> 00:29:18,441
I haven't thought about that
for years.

666
00:29:18,561 --> 00:29:19,721
It's something to do
with this message.

667
00:29:19,841 --> 00:29:23,401
He had to send it to you
before the Judoon got to him.

668
00:29:23,521 --> 00:29:26,081
What did he know?

669
00:29:26,201 --> 00:29:27,521
Are you sure it's your home?

670
00:29:27,641 --> 00:29:28,641
Of course I'm sure!

671
00:29:28,761 --> 00:29:30,841
I know...where I was
brought up.

672
00:29:31,921 --> 00:29:34,681
My parents are buried there,
on the land outside.

673
00:29:37,121 --> 00:29:40,481
I haven't thought about them
for years, either.

674
00:29:40,601 --> 00:29:43,041
- Do you know how to get there?
- Course I do.

675
00:29:43,161 --> 00:29:45,081
Then we're going,
me and you, now.

676
00:29:47,801 --> 00:29:49,561
Ship's security
is fighting back.

677
00:29:49,681 --> 00:29:52,001
You gotta be kidding me!

678
00:29:53,001 --> 00:29:55,041
Anti-theft attack system.

679
00:29:55,161 --> 00:29:57,801
Oh! Well, now I'm offended.

680
00:29:57,921 --> 00:29:59,641
Look, guys, I'm sorry,
I got get out of here.

681
00:29:59,761 --> 00:30:00,841
I got about a minute

682
00:30:00,961 --> 00:30:03,601
before the ship's nanogenes
attack my body.

683
00:30:03,721 --> 00:30:06,521
- What's going to happen to us?
- Oh!

684
00:30:06,641 --> 00:30:09,201
I'll pre-set the coordinates
to get you back.

685
00:30:09,321 --> 00:30:11,321
Just tell her this.

686
00:30:11,441 --> 00:30:13,361
I'm going to see her again.

687
00:30:13,481 --> 00:30:14,681
Maybe not soon.

688
00:30:14,801 --> 00:30:17,361
When she needs me,
I'll be there.

689
00:30:17,481 --> 00:30:18,921
In the meantime...

690
00:30:19,041 --> 00:30:20,921
...tell her...

691
00:30:21,041 --> 00:30:23,761
...beware the lone Cyberman.

692
00:30:27,041 --> 00:30:29,721
You don't know what a Cyberman
is yet, do you?

693
00:30:29,841 --> 00:30:31,281
No. What are they?

694
00:30:31,401 --> 00:30:33,401
An empire of evil...

695
00:30:33,521 --> 00:30:34,961
...in ruins right now...

696
00:30:36,121 --> 00:30:39,481
...brought down to nothing...

697
00:30:39,601 --> 00:30:40,841
...finally.

698
00:30:40,961 --> 00:30:42,721
But that could all change

699
00:30:42,841 --> 00:30:45,081
if she doesn't listen
to this message.

700
00:30:47,481 --> 00:30:49,321
To defeat them, the alliance

701
00:30:49,441 --> 00:30:53,801
sent this thing back
through time, across space.

702
00:30:54,801 --> 00:30:56,881
Agh! Oh!

703
00:30:57,001 --> 00:30:59,081
They are coming for me!

704
00:30:59,201 --> 00:31:02,041
Always the nanogenes!

705
00:31:02,161 --> 00:31:04,201
(CRIES OUT)

706
00:31:04,321 --> 00:31:06,921
I gotta go.
I've set the scoop for return.

707
00:31:07,041 --> 00:31:09,441
It should take you back
to where you were.

708
00:31:10,401 --> 00:31:13,961
Tell the Doctor...
the lone Cyberman.

709
00:31:15,281 --> 00:31:17,281
Don't give it what it wants.

710
00:31:17,401 --> 00:31:18,841
At all costs!

711
00:31:18,961 --> 00:31:20,601
Tell her!

712
00:31:21,361 --> 00:31:23,281
We've lost him!

713
00:31:24,361 --> 00:31:26,081
Are we stuck here now?

714
00:31:29,721 --> 00:31:31,521
I hope he's got
this thing right.

715
00:31:35,721 --> 00:31:37,281
Tell me about your parents.

716
00:31:37,401 --> 00:31:40,281
I wish I could tell you
I adored them.

717
00:31:40,401 --> 00:31:43,281
But they chose to live
in a disused lighthouse.

718
00:31:43,401 --> 00:31:46,241
That tells you how good
they were with people.

719
00:31:46,361 --> 00:31:48,281
Not like you,
in the heart of the city,

720
00:31:48,401 --> 00:31:49,881
talking to people
all day long.

721
00:31:50,001 --> 00:31:52,841
I guess we all rebel
against our parents.

722
00:31:52,961 --> 00:31:54,361
It's part of growing up, innit?

723
00:31:54,481 --> 00:31:56,521
Never been a fan of growing up.

724
00:31:56,641 --> 00:32:00,681
They loved it out here.
Suited them.

725
00:32:00,801 --> 00:32:02,921
Loved it so much
they wanted to be buried here?

726
00:32:03,041 --> 00:32:04,121
Yep.

727
00:32:04,241 --> 00:32:05,401
- You'd moved away by then.
- Yeah.

728
00:32:05,521 --> 00:32:07,361
But you still own
the lighthouse?

729
00:32:07,481 --> 00:32:09,001
Yeah, they left it to me.

730
00:32:09,121 --> 00:32:11,961
But I never wanted to
come back here to live, though.

731
00:32:15,041 --> 00:32:16,841
When did you move
to Gloucester?

732
00:32:16,961 --> 00:32:20,641
Ooh...1999.

733
00:32:20,761 --> 00:32:22,401
Mid-December.

734
00:32:24,401 --> 00:32:26,841
Are you testing me?

735
00:32:26,961 --> 00:32:28,361
Yes.

736
00:32:28,481 --> 00:32:31,001
I don't know
why I'm even trusting you.

737
00:32:31,121 --> 00:32:33,001
I've got one of those faces.

738
00:32:34,401 --> 00:32:36,001
I promise you...

739
00:32:36,121 --> 00:32:38,441
...I'm your best hope
of finding out who you are

740
00:32:38,561 --> 00:32:40,121
and staying alive.

741
00:32:42,041 --> 00:32:44,001
(ECHOING WHISPERS)

742
00:32:45,001 --> 00:32:46,361
Ruth?

743
00:32:49,481 --> 00:32:51,361
What are you seeing or hearing?

744
00:32:52,641 --> 00:32:54,001
Nothing.

745
00:32:55,081 --> 00:32:56,641
We're nearly there.

746
00:33:12,801 --> 00:33:13,841
That smell...

747
00:33:14,921 --> 00:33:16,161
...home.

748
00:33:18,681 --> 00:33:20,721
Forgotten what it feels
like to come back here.

749
00:33:22,121 --> 00:33:23,521
Like nothing can touch me.

750
00:33:25,121 --> 00:33:26,801
Mind if I take a look around?

751
00:33:30,441 --> 00:33:31,601
Sure.

752
00:33:33,721 --> 00:33:36,041
I'll get a fire going.

753
00:34:21,121 --> 00:34:22,121
(SONIC WHIRS)

754
00:34:36,721 --> 00:34:39,161
(ECHOING WHISPERS)

755
00:34:47,121 --> 00:34:49,521
Why have a blank gravestone?

756
00:34:49,641 --> 00:34:51,121
(SONIC WHIRS)

757
00:34:54,801 --> 00:34:56,361
Because it's not a grave.

758
00:35:01,281 --> 00:35:04,321
(ECHOING WHISPERS)

759
00:35:04,441 --> 00:35:07,281
(WHISPERS) Break the glass
and follow the light.

760
00:35:07,401 --> 00:35:09,921
Break the glass
and follow the light.

761
00:35:10,041 --> 00:35:12,121
(GRUNTS AND PANTS)

762
00:35:12,241 --> 00:35:14,121
Break the glass
and follow the light.

763
00:35:14,241 --> 00:35:16,121
Break the glass and follow
the light.

764
00:35:16,241 --> 00:35:18,401
Break the glass and...

765
00:35:18,521 --> 00:35:22,681
(WHOOSHING)

766
00:35:31,561 --> 00:35:33,161
(BUZZING)

767
00:35:34,521 --> 00:35:36,281
(PANTS HEAVILY)

768
00:35:40,601 --> 00:35:42,041
(WEAPON BEEPS)

769
00:36:01,041 --> 00:36:03,441
You're probably
a bit confused right now.

770
00:36:07,481 --> 00:36:09,161
I broke the glass.

771
00:36:09,281 --> 00:36:11,521
It's all come back to me.

772
00:36:12,801 --> 00:36:13,801
This.

773
00:36:15,761 --> 00:36:16,961
What is this?

774
00:36:18,041 --> 00:36:19,281
That's my ship.

775
00:36:20,321 --> 00:36:22,241
What?!

776
00:36:22,361 --> 00:36:25,121
Let me take it from the top.

777
00:36:25,241 --> 00:36:27,401
Hello, I'm The Doctor.

778
00:36:31,721 --> 00:36:34,481
I'm a traveller
in space and time,

779
00:36:34,601 --> 00:36:38,281
and that thing buried
down there is called a TARDIS.

780
00:36:38,401 --> 00:36:41,721
Time And Relative Dimension
In Space.

781
00:36:41,841 --> 00:36:44,081
You're gonna love this.

782
00:36:53,601 --> 00:36:56,001
Come on, old girl.

783
00:36:56,121 --> 00:36:58,241
Too sleepy.

784
00:36:58,361 --> 00:36:59,321
Power up!

785
00:36:59,441 --> 00:37:00,401
(TARDIS WARBLES)

786
00:37:00,521 --> 00:37:01,881
Need you right now.

787
00:37:04,121 --> 00:37:07,081
Hi. Struggling with this.
Can you just...?

788
00:37:07,201 --> 00:37:09,681
No, I can't. Not right now.
No time.

789
00:37:09,801 --> 00:37:12,321
Just stand there
and don't ask questions.

790
00:37:12,441 --> 00:37:14,961
Sorry you got caught up
in all this,

791
00:37:15,081 --> 00:37:17,241
but if Gat is half the
operative she used to be,

792
00:37:17,361 --> 00:37:19,041
she's already figured out
where we are.

793
00:37:19,161 --> 00:37:20,281
And we need to be ready,

794
00:37:20,401 --> 00:37:21,401
and we're not.

795
00:37:21,521 --> 00:37:22,721
Stop. Who's Gat?

796
00:37:22,841 --> 00:37:24,561
And who are you, really?

797
00:37:24,681 --> 00:37:25,761
Truly.

798
00:37:25,881 --> 00:37:27,561
I told you, love.
I'm The Doctor.

799
00:37:27,681 --> 00:37:29,761
- You can't be.
- Yeah? And why's that?

800
00:37:29,881 --> 00:37:31,441
Because I'm The Doctor.

801
00:37:34,121 --> 00:37:37,041
You have got to be kidding me!

802
00:37:38,321 --> 00:37:39,321
Really?

803
00:37:39,441 --> 00:37:40,561
Yes, really!

804
00:37:40,681 --> 00:37:41,761
Since when?

805
00:37:41,881 --> 00:37:43,441
Since forever.

806
00:37:43,561 --> 00:37:45,601
And how did I end up like...

807
00:37:45,721 --> 00:37:46,801
...that?

808
00:37:46,921 --> 00:37:49,801
All rainbows
and trousers that don't reach?

809
00:37:49,921 --> 00:37:51,961
What?
No, how did I end up like you?

810
00:37:52,081 --> 00:37:53,121
You don't.

811
00:37:53,241 --> 00:37:55,681
You're in my future,
not the other way round.

812
00:37:56,961 --> 00:37:58,401
I've never been
anything like you.

813
00:37:58,521 --> 00:38:00,561
Trust me, I'd remember.
Especially that shirt.

814
00:38:00,681 --> 00:38:03,281
So would I, if I'd ever
been you, which I haven't.

815
00:38:03,401 --> 00:38:04,601
DOCTOR: What?

816
00:38:06,201 --> 00:38:07,681
Huh?

817
00:38:08,921 --> 00:38:11,601
TOGETHER: That's not
possible. Unless it is.

818
00:38:11,721 --> 00:38:14,081
But what would that mean?
Doesn't make sense.

819
00:38:14,201 --> 00:38:15,321
Stop doing that!

820
00:38:15,441 --> 00:38:18,081
Oh. Same brain.

821
00:38:18,201 --> 00:38:20,801
No, this doesn't
make any sense.

822
00:38:20,921 --> 00:38:23,161
Either I should know you
or you should know me.

823
00:38:23,281 --> 00:38:25,241
- Agreed.
- So why don't we?

824
00:38:25,361 --> 00:38:26,281
I don't know.

825
00:38:26,401 --> 00:38:28,841
Why don't you try asking that
cute little gizmo of yours?

826
00:38:28,961 --> 00:38:29,961
Yeah, that's the one.

827
00:38:30,081 --> 00:38:31,841
I did. I used it on you,

828
00:38:31,961 --> 00:38:34,121
but it couldn't decrypt
the bio-shield.

829
00:38:34,241 --> 00:38:35,601
If you've been restored...

830
00:38:35,721 --> 00:38:36,681
(SONIC WHIRS)

831
00:38:36,801 --> 00:38:38,521
(SONIC CHIRPS)

832
00:38:39,601 --> 00:38:40,641
(SONIC WHIRS)

833
00:38:40,761 --> 00:38:42,241
(SONIC CHIRPS)

834
00:38:42,361 --> 00:38:43,401
Same person.

835
00:38:43,521 --> 00:38:44,881
Oh, no.

836
00:38:45,001 --> 00:38:46,681
But you don't recognise
the sonic screwdriver.

837
00:38:46,801 --> 00:38:48,161
Smart enough not to need one.

838
00:38:48,281 --> 00:38:51,041
Oh, yeah, nothing screams
"smart" like a laser rifle.

839
00:38:51,161 --> 00:38:52,641
I stored that before hiding,

840
00:38:52,761 --> 00:38:55,801
cos I knew Gat would come
one day, and now she has.

841
00:38:55,921 --> 00:38:57,121
Who is this Gat?

842
00:38:58,161 --> 00:38:59,841
I worked for her once.

843
00:38:59,961 --> 00:39:01,841
- You've got a job?
- Oh, sort of.

844
00:39:01,961 --> 00:39:04,121
Not one you apply for.
Not one you can ever leave.

845
00:39:04,241 --> 00:39:05,401
Believe me, I tried.

846
00:39:05,521 --> 00:39:07,361
You've been hiding on Earth.

847
00:39:07,481 --> 00:39:11,801
You used the Chameleon Arch
to hide your identity,

848
00:39:11,921 --> 00:39:14,641
to hide your mind,
even from yourself.

849
00:39:14,761 --> 00:39:16,561
That's why the sonic
didn't pick it up!

850
00:39:16,681 --> 00:39:17,961
And Lee was your protector.

851
00:39:18,081 --> 00:39:19,881
(CONDESCENDING) Well done.

852
00:39:20,001 --> 00:39:22,001
You're only five minutes behind
someone who just had

853
00:39:22,121 --> 00:39:24,121
their memory fully restored.
(GASPS) Five points.

854
00:39:24,241 --> 00:39:26,761
Don't do points, I do points.
Points are my thing.

855
00:39:26,881 --> 00:39:28,041
- (CRASHING)
- Oh!

856
00:39:28,161 --> 00:39:29,761
(CRACKLING)

857
00:39:29,881 --> 00:39:32,001
- (RUMBLING)
- What's happening?

858
00:39:32,121 --> 00:39:33,161
She's here.

859
00:39:36,561 --> 00:39:38,721
RUTH: The Judoon have got us
in a tractor beam,

860
00:39:38,841 --> 00:39:40,601
dragging us aboard their ship.

861
00:39:44,641 --> 00:39:47,561
Now listen to me, Doctor.

862
00:39:47,681 --> 00:39:50,001
Let me do the talking.

863
00:39:50,121 --> 00:39:51,521
Do not get involved.

864
00:39:51,641 --> 00:39:54,481
Because, if you really are me,
and Gat figures that?

865
00:39:54,601 --> 00:39:56,321
She'll kill us both.

866
00:39:57,561 --> 00:39:59,361
(RIFLE BEEPS)

867
00:40:05,041 --> 00:40:06,041
(DOOR CREAKS)

868
00:40:11,401 --> 00:40:13,921
GAT: Here we are, then.
End of the road.

869
00:40:15,681 --> 00:40:18,241
I thought I'd be angry
when I saw you.

870
00:40:19,881 --> 00:40:21,761
Turns out I'm just sorry.

871
00:40:21,881 --> 00:40:24,721
Not as sorry
as I'm about to be.

872
00:40:24,841 --> 00:40:26,961
Ruth, put it down.

873
00:40:27,081 --> 00:40:30,161
Yes, "Ruth”.
Do as your little friend says.

874
00:40:31,201 --> 00:40:32,961
You are surrounded, after all.

875
00:40:45,401 --> 00:40:47,521
Don't point that thing at me,
Gat.

876
00:40:47,641 --> 00:40:48,721
This was mine - you stole it.

877
00:40:48,841 --> 00:40:50,721
Mm, confiscated it.

878
00:40:52,321 --> 00:40:54,401
No, really,
don't point it at me.

879
00:40:54,521 --> 00:40:55,921
Perfect for your execution.

880
00:40:56,041 --> 00:40:57,521
I really wouldn't do that, Gat.

881
00:40:57,641 --> 00:40:59,521
Enough now.
Let's get off this rust bucket

882
00:40:59,641 --> 00:41:01,121
and finish this on my ship.

883
00:41:01,241 --> 00:41:02,761
- When you say "finish this"?
- Shut up.

884
00:41:02,881 --> 00:41:04,561
Take her advice, little woman.

885
00:41:04,681 --> 00:41:05,801
"Little"?

886
00:41:06,961 --> 00:41:07,961
Biting my tongue.

887
00:41:08,081 --> 00:41:10,561
Contract states Judoon
must deliver fugitive

888
00:41:10,681 --> 00:41:12,361
to contractee at Division.

889
00:41:12,481 --> 00:41:14,161
I'm here on behalf
of the contractee!

890
00:41:14,281 --> 00:41:16,241
Hang on, I thought you'd
hired the Judoon.

891
00:41:16,361 --> 00:41:17,441
- Who are you?
-I'm...

892
00:41:17,561 --> 00:41:18,921
Imperial Regulator.

893
00:41:19,041 --> 00:41:21,281
Sort of. Bit of a fib. Sorry.

894
00:41:21,401 --> 00:41:22,761
- Actually, I'm...
- She's nobody.

895
00:41:22,881 --> 00:41:24,641
Fine.

896
00:41:24,761 --> 00:41:26,161
I'm nobody.

897
00:41:26,281 --> 00:41:27,321
Absolutely nobody.

898
00:41:27,441 --> 00:41:28,601
See, I know why you want her -

899
00:41:28,721 --> 00:41:30,441
you've got a contract,
fair enough. But you?

900
00:41:30,561 --> 00:41:33,001
You want her dead
because she left her job?

901
00:41:33,121 --> 00:41:34,281
Shut up!

902
00:41:34,401 --> 00:41:35,641
Is that what she told you?

903
00:41:37,041 --> 00:41:39,041
This goes way higher than me.

904
00:41:39,161 --> 00:41:40,601
So, who would that be?

905
00:41:40,721 --> 00:41:42,641
Who are you all
ultimately working for?

906
00:41:42,761 --> 00:41:44,841
I'd really like to know.
Really.

907
00:41:44,961 --> 00:41:46,761
Information confidential.

908
00:41:46,881 --> 00:41:49,601
I told you to keep quiet!

909
00:41:49,721 --> 00:41:51,121
And look where
that's gotten us -

910
00:41:51,241 --> 00:41:52,361
lots of guns in lots of faces.

911
00:41:52,481 --> 00:41:53,681
And have you got
a better idea?

912
00:41:53,801 --> 00:41:55,961
I do, actually. My favourite -

913
00:41:56,081 --> 00:41:58,241
the curve ball and the Judoon.

914
00:41:59,401 --> 00:42:00,601
You wanted to find The Doctor?

915
00:42:00,721 --> 00:42:01,681
Don't you dare.

916
00:42:01,801 --> 00:42:02,721
Well, here I am.

917
00:42:02,841 --> 00:42:04,441
Will you be quiet?!

918
00:42:04,561 --> 00:42:06,721
Go on, scan me.

919
00:42:09,041 --> 00:42:10,841
(SCANNER BEEPS)

920
00:42:11,961 --> 00:42:13,201
Fugitive match positive.

921
00:42:13,321 --> 00:42:16,761
(SCANNER BEEPS)

922
00:42:16,881 --> 00:42:18,361
Fugitive match positive.

923
00:42:19,601 --> 00:42:23,201
Is there even a word
for how dumb you are?

924
00:42:23,321 --> 00:42:24,641
"Doctor"?

925
00:42:24,761 --> 00:42:26,841
Subsection 951 triggered.

926
00:42:26,961 --> 00:42:29,361
Two fugitives, two payments.

927
00:42:29,481 --> 00:42:31,441
There won't be two payments,

928
00:42:31,561 --> 00:42:32,841
because two
of the same Time Lord

929
00:42:32,961 --> 00:42:34,801
can't occupy the same space
at the same time.

930
00:42:34,921 --> 00:42:37,441
It's an abomination!
It'll destroy the time streams

931
00:42:37,561 --> 00:42:39,601
before you get
anywhere near Gallifrey!

932
00:42:39,721 --> 00:42:40,801
What did you say?

933
00:42:43,561 --> 00:42:45,241
(SONIC WHIRS)

934
00:42:45,361 --> 00:42:46,881
(SONIC CHIRPS)

935
00:42:47,001 --> 00:42:48,681
Gallifreyan.

936
00:42:48,801 --> 00:42:50,121
You're from home.

937
00:42:50,241 --> 00:42:52,641
I serve for the glory
of Gallifrey.

938
00:42:52,761 --> 00:42:55,201
Then both of you
can only be my past.

939
00:42:57,001 --> 00:42:58,801
But that's impossible,
because I know my own past -

940
00:42:58,921 --> 00:43:00,401
I lived through it. All of it.

941
00:43:00,521 --> 00:43:01,841
You're wrong.

942
00:43:01,961 --> 00:43:02,961
DOCTOR: I'm not wrong!

943
00:43:03,081 --> 00:43:05,201
I've seen Gallifrey destroyed.
Twice.

944
00:43:05,321 --> 00:43:06,281
First by a war,

945
00:43:06,401 --> 00:43:09,561
second by a lunatic
who I'm still trying to find.

946
00:43:09,681 --> 00:43:13,161
In my time,
Gallifrey doesn't exist.

947
00:43:14,241 --> 00:43:16,721
It's gone! Forever.

948
00:43:16,841 --> 00:43:20,201
And if you don't know that,
you're in my past.

949
00:43:20,321 --> 00:43:23,921
So you are only serving
at the glory of ash and bone.

950
00:43:24,041 --> 00:43:25,761
This is a trick.

951
00:43:25,881 --> 00:43:28,961
Check my mind -
one Time Lord to another.

952
00:43:29,081 --> 00:43:30,601
See what I saw.

953
00:43:32,041 --> 00:43:33,041
Keep an eye on her.

954
00:43:37,041 --> 00:43:37,961
Contact.

955
00:43:38,081 --> 00:43:40,841
(FIRES CRACKLE)

956
00:43:40,961 --> 00:43:43,641
RUTH: What did you see?

957
00:43:45,761 --> 00:43:46,761
What did she show you?

958
00:43:48,161 --> 00:43:49,601
I don't know
what trickery this is...

959
00:43:49,721 --> 00:43:50,641
(RIFLE BEEPS)

960
00:43:50,761 --> 00:43:52,441
Put the gun down, Gat.

961
00:43:52,561 --> 00:43:53,561
...but it ends here!

962
00:43:53,681 --> 00:43:56,241
Don't do this.

963
00:43:56,361 --> 00:43:57,441
(CRACKLING)

964
00:43:57,561 --> 00:43:59,721
(GASPS)

965
00:44:01,401 --> 00:44:03,241
You knew that would happen.

966
00:44:03,361 --> 00:44:04,641
You sabotaged the gun.

967
00:44:04,761 --> 00:44:07,321
I told her not to do it,
I begged her not to fire.

968
00:44:07,441 --> 00:44:08,641
But you knew she would!

969
00:44:08,761 --> 00:44:10,961
Don't take the moral
high ground with me.

970
00:44:11,081 --> 00:44:12,801
Crime has been witnessed.

971
00:44:12,921 --> 00:44:13,801
RUTH: No crime.

972
00:44:13,921 --> 00:44:15,401
- (SNARLS)
- An accident.

973
00:44:15,521 --> 00:44:19,601
And, besides, a Judoonese
Talwak Freighter like this,

974
00:44:19,721 --> 00:44:22,161
moving at 80 million clicks
an hour,

975
00:44:22,281 --> 00:44:24,681
entered interstellar space...

976
00:44:24,801 --> 00:44:26,201
...12 seconds ago.

977
00:44:27,321 --> 00:44:32,441
No-one has jurisdiction
in interstellar space.

978
00:44:32,561 --> 00:44:36,521
So no laws, and no crime.

979
00:44:36,641 --> 00:44:38,441
Isn't that right, Doctor?

980
00:44:40,881 --> 00:44:42,441
Yes.

981
00:44:42,561 --> 00:44:44,601
- (RIFLE BEEPS)
- Recalibrated.

982
00:44:44,721 --> 00:44:46,081
Who wants some?

983
00:44:46,201 --> 00:44:48,321
The Doctor never uses weapons.

984
00:44:48,441 --> 00:44:50,041
I know. Shut up!

985
00:44:51,361 --> 00:44:53,081
We're leaving now.

986
00:44:53,201 --> 00:44:54,841
(GROWLS)

987
00:44:54,961 --> 00:44:59,241
If you know what's good for
you, do /70t come for me again.

988
00:44:59,361 --> 00:45:01,041
Ever.

989
00:45:01,161 --> 00:45:05,201
Consider your
contract cancelled.

990
00:45:05,321 --> 00:45:06,401
(SNARLS)

991
00:45:06,521 --> 00:45:09,761
JUDOON: Judoon contracts will
always be fulfilled!

992
00:45:14,001 --> 00:45:16,281
Homing in your TARDIS signal.

993
00:45:17,521 --> 00:45:18,881
Can't get too close.

994
00:45:19,001 --> 00:45:21,241
Imagine the temporal
feedback loop.

995
00:45:22,801 --> 00:45:24,401
I'll drop you at the docks
near my flat.

996
00:45:24,521 --> 00:45:26,081
How's that?

997
00:45:26,201 --> 00:45:27,721
You can't be me.

998
00:45:29,001 --> 00:45:30,881
I know what I've done,
I know my own life.

999
00:45:31,001 --> 00:45:32,481
One of us has to be wrong.

1000
00:45:32,601 --> 00:45:34,601
(TARDIS THRUMS)

1001
00:45:36,401 --> 00:45:38,521
(THUD)

1002
00:45:40,521 --> 00:45:42,801
I'd quite like it
if you got off my ship now.

1003
00:45:45,921 --> 00:45:46,921
YAZ: There she is!

1004
00:45:48,161 --> 00:45:49,681
Doctor! Found you.

1005
00:45:50,961 --> 00:45:53,241
RYAN: Hey, what happened?
Where you been?

1006
00:45:53,361 --> 00:45:56,241
What happened to Ruth?
The Judoon things are gone.

1007
00:45:56,361 --> 00:45:57,641
You're never going to guess
what happened to us.

1008
00:45:57,761 --> 00:45:59,401
Captain Jack Harkness
said hello.

1009
00:45:59,521 --> 00:46:01,161
What?

1010
00:46:01,281 --> 00:46:03,161
GRAHAM: "Beware
the lone Cyberman.

1011
00:46:03,281 --> 00:46:06,761
"Do not let it have
what it wants, at all costs.”

1012
00:46:06,881 --> 00:46:08,001
That's all he said?

1013
00:46:08,121 --> 00:46:09,441
RYAN: Yeah, he got interrupted.

1014
00:46:09,561 --> 00:46:10,561
YAZ: Who is he, anyway?

1015
00:46:11,801 --> 00:46:13,081
An old friend.

1016
00:46:13,201 --> 00:46:14,521
I liked him.

1017
00:46:14,641 --> 00:46:16,481
Kinda cheesy.

1018
00:46:16,601 --> 00:46:18,121
But good cheesy.

1019
00:46:18,241 --> 00:46:19,481
That's Jack.

1020
00:46:20,601 --> 00:46:22,881
He didn't say any more
about the Cybermen?

1021
00:46:23,001 --> 00:46:25,241
Er, he said that
they were fallen empire

1022
00:46:25,361 --> 00:46:26,921
and they should stay that way.

1023
00:46:28,361 --> 00:46:30,601
What are they, these Cybermen?

1024
00:46:30,721 --> 00:46:32,801
They're one of the most
dangerous species

1025
00:46:32,921 --> 00:46:35,521
I've ever encountered,
up there with the Daleks.

1026
00:46:35,641 --> 00:46:37,881
Oh, I can't wait to meet then,
then.

1027
00:46:38,001 --> 00:46:39,321
And they're in our future?

1028
00:46:39,441 --> 00:46:41,601
They're always somewhere...

1029
00:46:42,761 --> 00:46:43,921
...waiting.

1030
00:46:44,041 --> 00:46:47,801
You haven't told us about Lee
and Ruth and the Judoon.

1031
00:46:47,921 --> 00:46:49,761
Who was the fugitive?

1032
00:46:53,481 --> 00:46:54,561
It was Ruth.

1033
00:46:56,481 --> 00:46:58,441
But Ruth was me.

1034
00:46:58,561 --> 00:46:59,601
What?

1035
00:47:00,681 --> 00:47:02,321
What are you talking about?

1036
00:47:02,441 --> 00:47:03,521
How's that possible?

1037
00:47:03,641 --> 00:47:07,601
She said she was my past,
but I know my past.

1038
00:47:07,721 --> 00:47:09,081
And she's never been me.

1039
00:47:09,201 --> 00:47:11,161
I'm sure there's
a simple explanation.

1040
00:47:12,241 --> 00:47:15,281
Time is swirling around me.

1041
00:47:15,401 --> 00:47:19,161
The Master,
Captain Jack Harkness, Ruth.

1042
00:47:21,881 --> 00:47:23,601
Something's coming for me.

1043
00:47:25,041 --> 00:47:26,121
I can feel it.

1044
00:47:26,241 --> 00:47:27,841
Let it come.

1045
00:47:27,961 --> 00:47:29,001
You've got us.

1046
00:47:29,121 --> 00:47:30,641
Ryan...

1047
00:47:31,721 --> 00:47:35,041
...I've lived for thousands of
years, so long I've lost count.

1048
00:47:35,161 --> 00:47:37,761
I've had so many faces.
How long have you been here?

1049
00:47:39,241 --> 00:47:40,521
You don't know me.

1050
00:47:41,801 --> 00:47:43,081
Not even a little bit.

1051
00:47:43,201 --> 00:47:44,401
Don't talk to him like that!

1052
00:47:44,521 --> 00:47:45,961
Yeah, I'm not having that.

1053
00:47:46,081 --> 00:47:47,881
We do know who you are.

1054
00:47:48,001 --> 00:47:50,121
You're the woman
that brought us together,

1055
00:47:50,241 --> 00:47:53,161
the woman that saved us
and loads of other people.

1056
00:47:57,041 --> 00:47:59,121
You're The Doctor.

1057
00:48:00,841 --> 00:48:03,641
Whoever you were in the past
or are in the future,

1058
00:48:03,761 --> 00:48:06,041
we know who you are right now.

1059
00:48:06,161 --> 00:48:07,281
Right?

1060
00:48:07,401 --> 00:48:08,561
Right!

1061
00:48:08,681 --> 00:48:10,561
The best person we know.

1062
00:48:10,681 --> 00:48:13,961
And whatever is coming
for you, we'll be here.

1063
00:48:14,081 --> 00:48:15,241
Cos we're your mates.

1064
00:48:15,361 --> 00:48:17,961
Well, not just mates. Family.

1065
00:48:18,081 --> 00:48:19,081
- Yeah.
- Yeah.

1066
00:48:20,761 --> 00:48:23,041
So, whether you
want to go looking

1067
00:48:23,161 --> 00:48:24,521
for whatever trouble's coming,

1068
00:48:24,641 --> 00:48:26,161
or whether you want
to wait here

1069
00:48:26,281 --> 00:48:27,761
and let it come to you...

1070
00:48:29,001 --> 00:48:31,121
...we'll be right here,
by your side,

1071
00:48:31,241 --> 00:48:33,441
like it or not, Doctor.

1072
00:48:33,561 --> 00:48:35,761
(ALARM BLARES)

1073
00:48:35,881 --> 00:48:37,641
What's that?

1074
00:48:37,761 --> 00:48:39,041
I know what you're doing -

1075
00:48:39,161 --> 00:48:40,961
siding with them,
distracting me.

1076
00:48:41,081 --> 00:48:43,281
You're doing this deliberately.

1077
00:48:43,401 --> 00:48:44,881
Whoa!

1078
00:48:45,001 --> 00:48:48,521
Multiple alerts across
three continents here on Earth.

1079
00:48:48,641 --> 00:48:51,121
Can't be connected.
Unless they are.

1080
00:48:51,241 --> 00:48:52,241
Quick look?

1081
00:48:53,921 --> 00:48:55,601
Quick look.

1082
00:48:55,721 --> 00:48:57,561
Let's go.

1083
00:49:28,561 --> 00:49:30,481
Need some help over here!

1084
00:49:30,601 --> 00:49:33,641
Two identical deaths
on two different continents.

1085
00:49:33,761 --> 00:49:36,361
It's even more dangerous
than I thought.

1086
00:49:36,481 --> 00:49:37,761
This can't be happening.

